0.0.1.3

AUTHORS

Kostya Zolotarov <kostya.zolotarov@gmail.com>

BACKGROUND

I need a tool to automate creation and maintenance of source code modules.
Invoked from command line, such tool would produce a source code module.
Produced source code module would contain a fixed set of empty boilerplate
files. The boilerplate files would describe the source code module and define
its format and structure. Example boilerplate files could be - README, INSTALL,
CHANGELOG, VERSION, etc.

DESCRIPTION

Command-line utility for automated creation and maintenance of source code
modules.

SOURCES

Source code can be obtained on GitHub (https://github.com/kz9676/srcmod).

Presently, I have one active branch:

    * origin/development  - is the main branch where the source code of HEAD
                            always reflects a state with the latest delivered
                            development changes for the next release

I often use supporting branches to aid parallel development, tracking of
features, preparation for production release and quick fixes for live
production defects. Supporting branches may include the following:

    * Feature branches
    * Release branches
    * Hotfix branches

